 lieutenant, author, and academic*1926 ;ndash; Bill Blackbeard, American historian and author (d. 2011)*  1926   ;ndash; Harper Lee, American author (d. 2016)*  1926   ;ndash; Hulusi Sayın, Turkish general (d. 1991)*1928 ;ndash; Yves Klein, French painter (d. 1962)*  1928   ;ndash; Eugene Merle Shoemaker, American geologist and astronomer (d. 1997)*1930 ;ndash; James Baker, American lawyer and politician, 61st United States Secretary of State*  1930   ;ndash; Carolyn Jones, American actress (d. 1983)*  1930   ;ndash; Richard C. Sarafian, American actor, director, and screenwriter (d. 2013)*1932 ;ndash; Brownie Ledbetter, American activist (d. 2010)*1933 ;ndash; Miodrag Radulovacki, Serbian-American neuropharmacologist and academic (d. 2014)*1934 ;ndash; Lois Duncan, American journalist and author*  1934   ;ndash; Diane Johnson, American-French author and screenwriter*1935 ;ndash; Jimmy Wray, Scottish boxer and politician (d. 2013)*1936 ;ndash; Tariq Aziz, Iraqi journalist and politician, Iraqi Minister of Foreign Affairs (d. 2015)*1937 ;ndash; Saddam Hussein, Iraqi general and politician, 5th President of Iraq (d. 2006)*  1937   ;ndash; Jean Redpath, Scottish-American singer-songwriter (d. 2014)*  1937   ;ndash; John White, Scottish footballer (d. 1964)*1938 ;ndash; Fred Dibnah, English steeplejack and television personality (d. 2004)*  1938   ;ndash; Madge Sinclair, Jamaican-American actress (d. 1995)*1941 ;ndash; Ann-Margret, Swedish-American actress, singer, and dancer*  1941   ;ndash; Lucien Aimar, French cyclist*  1941   ;ndash; Indus Arthur, American actress and singer (d. 1984)*  1941   ;ndash; John Madejski, English businessman and academic*  1941   ;ndash; Nico Mastorakis, Greek director and producer*  1941   ;ndash; Flynn Robinson,  American basketball player (d. 2013)*  1941   ;ndash; Karl Barry Sharpless, American chemist and academic, Nobel Prize laureate*  1941   ;ndash; Iryna Zhylenko, Ukrainian poet and author (d. 2013)*1942 ;ndash; Mike Brearley, En